@startuml
!theme plain

title Enrollment Status Lifecycle

[*] --> NotEnrolled : Initial State

NotEnrolled --> Enrolled : student enrolls\n(enrollment_date recorded)

state Enrolled {
  state "Active Enrollment" as Active
  state "Classes Ongoing" as Classes
  state "Exams Completed" as ExamsDone
}

Enrolled --> Dropped : student drops course\nor admin removes
Enrolled --> Completed : semester ends\nmarks finalized

Dropped --> [*] : Final State
Completed --> [*] : Final State

note right of Enrolled
**Enrolled State Details:**
• Student can attend classes
• Faculty can mark attendance
• Marks can be entered
• Transcript can be updated
end note

note right of Dropped
**Dropped State:**
• No further actions
• Cannot re-enroll same section
• Record maintained for history
end note

note right of Completed
**Completed State:**
• Marks finalized
• Grade assigned
• Transcript entry created
• GPA calculated
end note
@enduml